"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-20-IOC-Refugee-Olympic-Team-arrives-at-Athletes-Village-1vnYkvzmRQQ-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  The Refugee Olympic Team of the International Olympic Committee (IOC) has arrived at the Athletes Village in the suburbs of Paris.  A total of 37 athletes from 15 nations and regions comprise this year's Refugee Olympic Team, and they will participate in 12 events at the Games.  Before making their way to the French capital, the athletes gathered in Normandy for a welcome event that allowed them to meet their teammates, and train at the state-of-the-art facilities in Bayeux.  The Refugee Olympic Team's tweet on July 20 about their arrival in Paris. /@RefugeesOlympic  Paris 2024 will mark the third appearance of the Refugee Olympic Team at the Games, after 29 athletes competed in Tokyo and an inaugural 10-member squad debuted eight years ago in Rio.  IOC MEDIA's tweet on July 16 about the Refugee Olympic Team's gathering in Bayeux. /@iocmedia  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"